                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G/241: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-04T13:00:00-03:00"
                            >October 4, 1933—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 4—11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>86. Informed in confidence that one of the questions to be discussed during visit
                    of Argentine President and Minister for Foreign Affairs end of this week is
                    whether Pan American Conference should be held as scheduled or postponed.
                    Brazilian Minister for Foreign Affairs tells me he is convinced it is folly to
                    hold Conference with Chaco and Leticia disputes still unsettled and Cuban
                    situation in aggravated state.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
